'''Vanster Enan's Sop House''' was a [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] located in [[Gadrin]]. It was one of the liveliest and loudest cantinas on [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]], being on a supply route from the river to the docking bays in [[Hedrett]]. It was usually known for raucous music. The house special was a "fine [[Ithorian brandy]]," which was actually a homebrew which [[Vanster Enan]], an [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]], made from Cularin tree sap.<ref name="ACP">{{LivingForce|Eye of the Sun: A Cularin Presence}}</ref>

On the 200th anniversary of [[Reidi Artom]]'s founding of Gadrin, a young man named [[Darin]] burst into the Sop House crying out that Cularin was in danger. He was followed by security guards in [[House Hirskaala]] uniforms who arrested him and took him away. This instigated some of the Sop House's patrons to look into the matter, which ended with them uncovering and bringing down a [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] ring.<ref name="ACP" />

The Sop House was also a site of much partying during a celebration over the defeat of the [[Metatheran Cartel]] a little over a month later.<ref name="AUP">{{LivingForce|An Uneasy Peace}}</ref> It sent representation to the [[SoroSuub Anniversary celebration, 31 BBY]] in [[Genarius]].<ref name="BW">''[[Blown Away]]'' (as described in [https://web.archive.org/web/20021218152817/www.wizards.com/rpga/livingforce/article.asp?x=lf/swlf20010927b_transmissions&c=swlfc Transmissions From the Living Force Campaign] on the [[Wikipedia:Internet Archive#Wayback machine|Way back machine]])</ref>

